{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fadcd363-07cc-4044-a523-f46844a3bc59","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests distinctly from passed/failed, and the reason string appears in test results output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cbb8e68b-ba29-4b3c-84be-c41dceec6a8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about test framework attributes. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":327,"requestId":"702C:162674:B28438:CE7F26:69F2AC88"},"id":"40ac4815-37f9-43ad-aacf-851d31dbbac1","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:12:46.926Z","parentId":"86e9deea-7f6a-4c36-8335-ef60e070eb8c"}
